    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-07-01T17:28:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-07-01T17:28:00-05:00" n="365"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                <head>365. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Republic of the Congo</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d365fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, POL 17 US-AFR. Secret. Drafted by High, cleared by Starrs, and
                        approved by Whitehouse. Repeated to Lisbon, <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                            >USUN</gloss>, Paris for <persName corresp="#p_CH4"
                        >Cleveland</persName>, and Luanda.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-07-01T18:28:00-04:00">July 1, 1963, 6:28 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 3198. General instructions contacts
                    with Port African nationalists contained CA-14448, June 24.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d365fn1">Airgram CA-14448 to Algiers, Conakry, Dakar, Dar-es-Salaam,
                        Elisabethville, Leopoldville, Rabat, Salisbury, and <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                            >USUN</gloss>, June 24. (Ibid.)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Gist of instruction: you should not initiate or seek out contacts with these
                    nationalists. If they ask see Embassy officer, should be received by officers
                    other than Ambassador, preferably at Pol Officer level. Since <gloss
                        target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> has post at Leo, Port Embassy should be
                    informed after meetings <pb facs="0596" n="568" xml:id="pg_568"/> that
                    nationalists seen at their request, but no indication of substance should be
                    given.</p>
                <p>If nationalists press to see Ambassador and Ambassador believes direct contact by
                    him desirable, he should submit appropriate justification and request prior
                    authorization from Dept.</p>
                <p>If Embassy officers meet <persName corresp="#p_RH3">Holden Roberto</persName>
                    socially or otherwise, they may of course converse with him. Utmost discretion
                    required in such contacts. These occasions need not be reported to Port
                    Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Ball</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
